WEBVTT

00:02.737 --> 00:07.006
   (SOUND OF WATER DRIPPING)

00:16.784 --> 00:21.086
   (DRIPPING SOUND CONTINUES)

00:36.070 --> 00:40.239
       (SOFT JAZZ MUSIC)

00:48.182 --> 00:52.451
     (LIGHT CHURNING SOUND)

00:57.691 --> 01:02.528
  (SOFT JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:08.269 --> 01:12.671
   (DRIPPING SOUND CONTINUES)

01:18.813 --> 01:22.448
  (SOFT JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:32.393 --> 01:34.793
          ZOE: Action.

01:34.795 --> 01:37.229
       (EXPLOSION SOUND)

01:44.171 --> 01:46.338
             Cool.

01:46.340 --> 01:48.474
     Zoe, time for school!

01:48.476 --> 01:52.277
              ZOE
     I'm brushing my teeth!

02:02.123 --> 02:04.857
  (SOFT JAZZ MUSIC CONTINUES)

02:07.795 --> 02:15.534
        (SAWING SOUNDS)

02:15.536 --> 02:19.271
        (JAZZ CONTINUES
      WITH DRIPPING SOUND)

02:29.250 --> 02:32.351
  So I get a call at seven in
  the morning. And they say oh

02:32.353 --> 02:38.257
 by the way, Zoe needs to bring
 three dozen cupcakes to school

02:38.259 --> 02:42.494
   for a play this afternoon.
 This is seven am THIS morning

02:42.496 --> 02:45.364
    you understand. I've got
  an order of studs arriving,

02:45.366 --> 02:47.499
       I gotta be at the
  construction site by nine AM

02:47.501 --> 02:50.569
   so in my free time, sure,
  why not get in some baking?

02:51.672 --> 02:55.507
  Oh, and they gotta be pink.
 <i> Everything is pink right now.</i>

02:55.910 --> 02:56.909
        (BEEPING SOUND)

02:56.911 --> 02:59.912
             Oscar!

02:59.914 --> 03:01.613
Can I get a little help in here?

03:01.615 --> 03:04.683
    The waffles are burning.

03:13.394 --> 03:15.928
             OSCAR
            Um, Sal?

03:15.930 --> 03:19.198
 There's blood dripping through
   the ceiling fixture again.

03:22.269 --> 03:24.903
              Zoe!

03:29.510 --> 03:34.213
         (TRAIN SOUNDS)

03:40.921 --> 03:43.989
      SAL (VOICE MESSAGE)
  We re busy having a domestic
   disaster. Leave a message.

03:45.826 --> 03:48.627
             ZILLA
    Um, hi Dad, it's Zilla.

03:48.629 --> 03:51.263
     I just wanted to call
   and see how you re doing.

03:51.265 --> 03:53.932
      Actually, I thought
 I might come home for a visit.

03:53.934 --> 03:58.604
    Just to say hi. So, you
    know, pick up the phone.

04:04.245 --> 04:07.446
     Zoe! If you lock this
  thing one more time I swear

04:07.448 --> 04:09.281
       I will cut it off
       with a power saw.

04:09.283 --> 04:11.516
      You know this is for
      emergency use only.

04:11.518 --> 04:13.885
        When someone is
downstairs trying to murder you

04:13.887 --> 04:16.721
        you get to lock
     this door, not before.

04:16.724 --> 04:22.394
      Now I know you re in
 there. Come out of the closet.

04:22.396 --> 04:23.829
          Look at you.

04:23.831 --> 04:25.464
  It's the last day of school.

04:25.466 --> 04:27.966
      Can't you keep your
 uniform clean for ten seconds?

04:27.968 --> 04:31.336
 How does it reflect on me as a
father if you show up to school

04:31.338 --> 04:33.372
  covered in blood every day?

04:33.374 --> 04:36.441
            Come on,
  let's get you in the shower.

04:45.052 --> 04:47.052
             ZILLA
      Hi Dad, Zilla again.

04:47.054 --> 04:51.723
Look, I'd really like to talk to
     you before I get home.

04:51.725 --> 04:53.759
  Actually, I have some news.

04:53.761 --> 04:55.894
       I'm not pregnant.
 And I haven't been arrested...

04:55.896 --> 04:58.864
      So keep that in mind
  when you hear my news, okay?

04:58.866 --> 05:01.900
     It's important to keep
perspective about these things.

05:02.403 --> 05:05.671
   (TROLLEY SOUNDS ON TRACKS)

05:07.608 --> 05:10.309
      I can't believe all
    her school uniforms have

05:10.311 --> 05:11.310
      bloodstains on them.

05:11.312 --> 05:13.478
    Hey, it's not my fault.

05:13.480 --> 05:16.014
      Do I look like some
    kind of fashion expert?

05:16.016 --> 05:18.383
  There's a difference between
  identifying a fashion trend

05:18.385 --> 05:20.986
        and identifying
      a bloodstain, Oscar.

05:20.988 --> 05:23.655
      I forgot my costume!

05:23.657 --> 05:25.757
            -sighs-

05:25.758 --> 05:27.858
           I'm late.
  Can't you go on without it?

05:27.861 --> 05:30.062
      I can't be in a play
      without my costume.

05:30.064 --> 05:33.598
   It's the only thing we re
  doing today. Just the play.

05:33.600 --> 05:36.251
      I ll take her home.

05:36.252 --> 05:38.903
No you won't. She ll show up in
  some kind of ghoul ensemble.

05:38.906 --> 05:40.972
            I ll go.

05:44.611 --> 05:48.980
    (MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYS
     UNDER SOUND OF TRAIN)

05:57.958 --> 05:59.691
You forgot to bring your costume

05:59.693 --> 06:01.760
        or you forgot to
       make your costume?

06:01.762 --> 06:03.929
    You forgot the cupcakes.

06:03.931 --> 06:05.997
          Son of a...

06:13.140 --> 06:17.843
             Pink.

06:18.779 --> 06:21.446
          ZILLA: Dad?

06:21.448 --> 06:23.515
             Zilla?

06:24.852 --> 06:26.084
          What are you
    doing home from school?

06:26.086 --> 06:28.303
   We weren't expecting you.

06:28.304 --> 06:30.521
             ZILLA
     Actually Dad, there's
 something I have to tell you.

06:30.524 --> 06:32.657
        You re pregnant.

06:32.659 --> 06:34.993
   You know, just because you
and Mom got pregnant in college

06:34.995 --> 06:36.728
     doesn't mean everyone
    makes the same mistake.

06:36.730 --> 06:38.130
  Not in front of your sister.

06:38.132 --> 06:39.131
     So- so you re not...?

06:39.133 --> 06:41.967
   No. No chance whatsoever.

06:41.969 --> 06:44.035
           Oh. Good!

06:44.037 --> 06:46.738
        Well we re in a
     huge hurry here, honey

06:46.740 --> 06:48.039
        so maybe we can
   talk later this afternoon-

06:48.041 --> 06:50.942
             ZILLA
Dad, I really need to talk now.

06:50.944 --> 06:53.445
        I need raw meat.

06:53.447 --> 06:55.514
         In the fridge.

06:56.984 --> 06:59.451
         Are you having
      problems at school?

06:59.453 --> 07:00.786
      And the internship?

07:00.788 --> 07:03.722
   I, um- I turned that down.

07:03.724 --> 07:06.158
       That was a really
    good internship, Zilla.

07:06.160 --> 07:08.160
    How are you supposed to
 get into a good med school if-

07:08.162 --> 07:10.695
  Look Dad, if you re going to
 freak out about the internship

07:10.697 --> 07:13.165
   you re really not going to
   be able to handle my news.

07:13.167 --> 07:16.352
       There's more news?

07:16.353 --> 07:19.538
 So there's this kind of crazy,
  angry PTA mom on the phone?

07:19.540 --> 07:22.607
   And she says that they re
   missing 36 pink cupcakes.

07:24.211 --> 07:27.479
   She seems to be under the
impression that you stole them.

07:30.150 --> 07:31.850
           Hi, Zilla.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.919
        Hi, Uncle Oscar.

07:33.921 --> 07:37.122
        Just- tell them
      they re on the way.

07:37.124 --> 07:41.493
   Could- could you just tell
 her? Frankly she's scary, bro.

07:41.495 --> 07:43.094
  Dad, we re going to be late!

07:43.096 --> 07:48.600
     Okay. Oscar, you take
    Zoe to school. Then call

07:48.602 --> 07:50.202
 the construction site and tell
  them we re going to be late.

07:50.204 --> 07:53.839
     Tell them there's been
  some kind of freak accident.

07:53.841 --> 07:56.908
     I ll tell them there's
been a kite boarding collision.

07:58.479 --> 08:01.012
           Whatever.

08:01.014 --> 08:04.082
        How do you feel
     about helping me bake?

08:11.024 --> 08:13.391
      This is disgusting.

08:13.392 --> 08:15.759
 They don't have to taste good,
honey, they just have to exist.

08:17.231 --> 08:18.763
      So what's your news?

08:18.765 --> 08:20.866
Before I tell you, I want you to
      promise that you ll

08:20.868 --> 08:22.985
        be happy for me.

08:22.986 --> 08:25.103
 How can I promise that, honey?
 I don't know what the news is.

08:26.106 --> 08:28.273
      Well, it's something
      that makes me happy.

08:28.275 --> 08:32.177
     Well frankly, I don't
   know what makes you happy.

08:32.179 --> 08:36.982
  I mean, maybe you've always
 wanted to be a trapeze artist.

08:36.984 --> 08:38.984
        I'm not going to
applaud you for leaving college

08:38.986 --> 08:40.652
      to join the circus.

08:40.654 --> 08:43.822
        Or maybe you met
    a handsome drug dealer.

08:43.823 --> 08:46.291
      I mean, just tell me
    what the news is honey.

08:46.293 --> 08:48.927
    Do you want me to guess?

08:48.929 --> 08:51.997
Well, the second one is closer.

08:56.270 --> 08:59.638
      You re squeezing out
    all the frosting, Zilla.

08:59.640 --> 09:02.107
 Now I don't have any frosting.

09:04.778 --> 09:06.895
            -sighs-

09:06.896 --> 09:09.013
      Okay, let's just say
 hypothetically I promise to be

09:09.016 --> 09:12.551
     happy with your news.
Hypothetically, in what category

09:12.553 --> 09:14.586
     would this news fall?

09:14.588 --> 09:19.090
        It would fall in
       the love category.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.259
         Oh God. That's
     worse than I thought.

09:21.261 --> 09:24.930
            CUSTOMER
  ..And I'd like some of those
orange ones with the sprinkles.

09:24.932 --> 09:27.198
Not the round orange sprinkles.

09:27.200 --> 09:29.885
        The cylindrical
       orange sprinkles.

09:29.886 --> 09:32.571
  Excuse me, is this something
that could possibly be sped up?

09:32.573 --> 09:35.206
    Because we re kind of in
a time sensitive situation here.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.776
     Excuse me, but I think
  I have as much of a right to

09:37.778 --> 09:40.312
  personalize my confectionery
       choices as you do.

09:40.314 --> 09:43.815
Oh, I'm not denying that right.
It's just that, well, we have to

09:43.817 --> 09:47.185
 get three dozen pink cupcakes
   in the next sixty seconds

09:47.187 --> 09:49.821
or I'm going to miss what's left
 of my daughter's school play.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.224
  Well, what kind of cupcakes?

09:52.225 --> 09:54.626
 We have raspberry strawberry,
    marionberry, red velvet-

09:54.628 --> 09:58.196
           Any kind!
      Just make them pink!

10:01.068 --> 10:04.603
         (DOOR BANGS,
     FOLLOWED BY FOOTSTEPS)

10:12.079 --> 10:15.080
 Now listen, Zilla. We have to
go in there and see what's left

10:15.082 --> 10:17.215
     of your sister's play,
    and if you don't tell me

10:17.217 --> 10:20.352
    what your news is first,
I will write you out of my will.

10:20.354 --> 10:23.622
   Fine. I'm getting married.

10:25.258 --> 10:26.958
             What?

10:26.960 --> 10:31.830
    Married? You re getting
 married? You are 21 years old.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.665
        You married Mom
       when you were 19!

10:33.667 --> 10:36.001
       Oh, and that was a
   brilliant idea, wasn't it?

10:36.003 --> 10:40.105
    I mean, do you see your
    mother around anywhere?

10:40.107 --> 10:42.273
      Have you heard from
  her in the past eight years?

10:42.275 --> 10:44.209
       You wouldn't even
    know what tenderness was

10:44.211 --> 10:45.761
       if it weren't for
       your Uncle Oscar!

10:45.762 --> 10:47.312
    I knew you were going to
 freak out. That's why I didn't

10:47.314 --> 10:50.115
    tell you over the phone!

10:52.152 --> 10:55.220
       This is absolutely
      out of the question!

11:04.297 --> 11:06.965
       Sorry. Excuse me.

11:12.105 --> 11:14.773
What's this play about, anyway?

11:14.775 --> 11:17.442
       American History.

11:17.444 --> 11:20.879
         Um, you missed
       most of the play.

11:20.881 --> 11:23.348
       They just have the
      costume awards left.

11:28.321 --> 11:30.455
   You are still in college.

11:30.457 --> 11:33.458
Is there some rule that college
   students can't be married?

11:33.460 --> 11:36.061
Have you ever thought about how
 hard it will be to get through

11:36.063 --> 11:37.696
       med school if you
      have kids to raise?

11:37.698 --> 11:39.264
That won't be a problem for us.

11:39.266 --> 11:41.733
   You can't necessarily plan
      these things, Zilla.

11:41.735 --> 11:45.270
      Birth control isn't
   always what it should be.

11:45.272 --> 11:47.839
           PRINCIPAL
    Thank you all for coming
  and joining us on this happy

11:47.841 --> 11:48.907
        family occasion.

11:48.909 --> 11:52.811
      -audience clapping-

11:52.813 --> 11:54.913
   I'd like to thank all the
    parents in the audience

11:54.915 --> 11:58.149
for all the effort that you put
into the baking and the costumes

11:58.151 --> 12:00.852
  and the students behind the
curtain for all their hard work.

12:00.854 --> 12:02.220
        I'm sure they re
   ready for summer vacation.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.756
        -KIDS cheering-

12:04.758 --> 12:07.225
       -audience laughs-

12:07.227 --> 12:10.328
 In recognition of some of the
 costumes that really stood out

12:10.330 --> 12:12.831
     we would like to give
    out a few quick prizes.

12:12.833 --> 12:16.101
       The prize for the
   prettiest costume goes to

12:16.103 --> 12:18.837
       Mary Ann Percy as
     the Statue of Liberty.

12:18.839 --> 12:23.775
       -audience cheers-

12:24.377 --> 12:28.046
      Next, the prize for
  the coolest costume goes to

12:28.048 --> 12:30.515
          Tyson Baker
   who came as a Rough Rider.

12:30.517 --> 12:33.785
       -audience cheers-

12:36.456 --> 12:41.493
 And, ah, our judges decided to
give out a third prize this year

12:44.131 --> 12:49.200
     The award for the most
   disturbing costume goes to

12:50.203 --> 12:53.171
          Zoe Balicki
who decided to come as a pilgrim

12:53.173 --> 12:57.275
         who has been..

12:57.277 --> 12:59.410
            scalped.

12:59.412 --> 13:02.480
        -quiet applause-

13:07.821 --> 13:11.156
            -crying-

13:11.158 --> 13:13.925
        Zoe, we have to
    applaud your creativity.

13:13.927 --> 13:17.362
        However, a quick
  reminder for Zoe's parents:

13:17.364 --> 13:20.365
 including, ah, raw meat on an

13:20.367 --> 13:26.104
  elementary school costume is
not considered strictly sanitary

13:26.106 --> 13:27.872
        And now, if the
    children will join me in

13:27.874 --> 13:29.941
    singing our school song.

13:36.149 --> 13:39.150
        I didn't finish
      telling you my news.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.820
    I'm sorry, there's more?

13:42.856 --> 13:47.425
     I invited my fiancée's
    family over for dinner.

13:47.427 --> 13:50.094
    I want you to meet her.

13:51.998 --> 13:55.300
     Beg your pardon. Her?

13:55.302 --> 13:58.369
      I'm a lesbian, Dad.

13:58.371 --> 13:59.370
             What?

13:59.372 --> 14:01.606
         I'm a lesbian!

14:15.322 --> 14:17.188
      So, this is how you

14:17.190 --> 14:20.091
        choose to share
 important news with the family

14:20.093 --> 14:23.294
       Just dumping it on
      us out of the blue.

14:23.296 --> 14:26.130
 Believe me, coming out in the
 middle of a grade school play

14:26.132 --> 14:29.334
    was not my ideal way of
coming out of the closet either.

14:29.336 --> 14:32.136
     Well, couldn't we have
 had a more gradual transition?

14:32.138 --> 14:34.539
      I mean, last I knew,
      you had a boyfriend.

14:34.541 --> 14:37.041
             OSCAR
       Yeah, isn't there
    supposed to be some like

14:37.043 --> 14:40.345
      I don't know, sexual
     experimentation first?

14:40.347 --> 14:41.346
        There has been.

14:41.348 --> 14:42.413
            Oh God.

14:42.415 --> 14:44.048
          Come on Dad,
    when's the last time you

14:44.050 --> 14:45.884
  actually saw me with a man?

14:45.886 --> 14:48.953
  There was that guy you went
 to the Fire & Ice dance with.

14:50.357 --> 14:52.124
       Was that a woman?

14:52.125 --> 14:53.892
        No Uncle Oscar,
     that was Bobby Milton

14:53.894 --> 14:56.060
        and that was in
       the eighth grade.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.462
            GRANDMA
        What's going on?

14:57.464 --> 14:59.898
     Zilla's a lesbian now!

14:59.900 --> 15:02.300
             ZILLA
       I've always been a
     lesbian, Uncle Oscar.

15:02.302 --> 15:05.103
      Well we re so sorry
     to offend you, Zilla.

15:05.105 --> 15:08.539
 We really apologize that your
family's been too insensitive to

15:08.541 --> 15:11.609
    notice, possibly because
    you've always dated men.

15:11.611 --> 15:14.345
  I knew you wouldn't approve.

15:14.347 --> 15:16.381
        It's not that I
       disapprove, honey.

15:16.383 --> 15:20.451
       It's just... well,
     it's all very sudden.

15:22.088 --> 15:24.055
           AUNT MARGE
    Sal told me everything.

15:24.057 --> 15:25.590
I brought you some chicken soup.

15:25.592 --> 15:28.159
            Okay...

15:28.161 --> 15:30.461
       You do understand
     that this is not like

15:30.463 --> 15:33.264
   a contagious disease that
can be treated with soup, right?

15:33.266 --> 15:36.167
         And I brought
     some dresses for Zoe.

15:36.169 --> 15:38.269
         Hello, Marge.

15:38.271 --> 15:42.106
      Sal. Troubled times.

15:42.108 --> 15:45.977
   This is what happens when
girls are raised without mothers

15:45.979 --> 15:48.079
  What, they become lesbians?

15:48.081 --> 15:52.583
  And Zoe! I heard she made a
 sensation at the school play.

15:52.585 --> 15:53.718
 How do you know these things?

15:53.720 --> 15:55.520
    I try to stay informed.

15:55.522 --> 15:58.489
 I've said it a million times.
 You've got to take better care

15:58.491 --> 16:01.092
        of these girls.
      You should remarry.

16:01.094 --> 16:04.395
      And I've told you a
      million times, Marge

16:04.397 --> 16:06.197
 I haven't met the right woman.

16:06.199 --> 16:09.267
   Maybe you re secretly gay.

16:28.755 --> 16:33.424
   (UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC STARTS)

16:55.181 --> 16:58.416
         (DOOR JINGLES)

17:03.356 --> 17:06.357
             DWAYNE
       Well, if it isn't
      the movie director.

17:06.358 --> 17:08.693
     How's the horror film
      coming, Ms. Kubrick?

17:08.694 --> 17:10.461
     Has my coffin arrived?

17:10.463 --> 17:12.262
       It came yesterday.
    I still don't know what

17:12.265 --> 17:14.148
    you want with a coffin.

17:14.150 --> 17:16.034
  Aren't you small, miniature
people supposed to be in school?

17:16.036 --> 17:17.786
         It's vacation.

17:17.787 --> 17:19.537
Then why aren't you out playing
   with your youthful peers?

17:19.539 --> 17:20.637
  Don't you have any friends?

17:20.640 --> 17:22.473
            Do you?

17:22.474 --> 17:23.641
            Touché.

17:23.643 --> 17:24.809
          Where is it?

17:24.810 --> 17:28.079
   In the back. I ll get it.

17:32.619 --> 17:36.788
    (MELANCHOLY JAZZ PLAYS)

17:51.771 --> 17:53.838
    This doesn't look real.

17:53.840 --> 17:56.507
     It's for magic shows.

18:01.147 --> 18:02.580
        This is stupid.

18:02.582 --> 18:05.249
    You order away, you pay.

18:10.323 --> 18:12.857
         You hear about
      the horror contest?

18:12.859 --> 18:14.792
 Hosted by the Film Foundation.

18:14.794 --> 18:16.727
      Hundred dollars cash
   prize for whoever turns in

18:16.729 --> 18:18.296
  the best short horror film.

18:18.298 --> 18:19.530
      When's the deadline?

18:19.532 --> 18:22.633
           July 1st.

18:22.635 --> 18:25.770
 It's for college kids, dummy!

18:25.772 --> 18:27.839
       You ll never win.

18:33.680 --> 18:37.448
    Okay, I think that we've
  all had enough time to think

18:37.450 --> 18:39.684
         about this new
     situation and adjust.

18:39.686 --> 18:42.420
  The important thing is that
 Lu's family is coming over for

18:42.422 --> 18:44.555
     dinner and we need to
    get ready to greet them.

18:44.557 --> 18:46.691
 What's this family like, dear?

18:46.693 --> 18:49.460
I guess they re sort of formal.

18:49.462 --> 18:52.563
   Formal? Like, how formal?

18:52.565 --> 18:54.699
         Well, they re
  conservatives from New York

18:54.701 --> 18:57.335
        so Lu says they
    always dress for dinner.

18:58.304 --> 18:59.737
         Dress in what?

18:59.739 --> 19:03.875
    Like, in clothes?  Cause
  we do that, we wear clothes.

19:03.877 --> 19:05.409
       The men wear ties.

19:05.411 --> 19:06.544
         How many men?

19:06.546 --> 19:09.413
   Um, Lu has three brothers,

19:09.415 --> 19:13.451
 so I guess there ll be eleven.

19:13.453 --> 19:15.286
            Eleven?

19:15.288 --> 19:17.889
  We don't have enough forks.

19:17.891 --> 19:21.659
       Fancy conservative
 types always have extra forks.

19:21.661 --> 19:25.196
    And they don't recycle.
  They hate environmentalists.

19:25.198 --> 19:26.430
          Well they re
      gonna love Portland.

19:26.432 --> 19:27.798
       You guys, please!

19:27.800 --> 19:29.901
         I'm asking you
       to do this for me.

19:29.903 --> 19:33.337
  Not because you support gays
 or conservatives or whatever.

19:33.339 --> 19:36.407
        But because you
    love and care about me.

19:43.716 --> 19:46.851
   If I start now, I can get
  three lasagnas in the oven.

19:46.853 --> 19:51.422
 I ll make a salad and take the
 Greenpeace signs off the lawn.

19:51.424 --> 19:53.891
     I will set the table.

19:56.930 --> 20:00.865
         Okay, you re a
     recently reincarnated

20:00.867 --> 20:04.635
 emotionally confused werewolf
 who hasn't had anything to eat

20:04.637 --> 20:06.938
   in ten centuries. Action!

20:06.940 --> 20:10.208
           -growling-

20:14.480 --> 20:16.948
             -howl-

20:25.325 --> 20:28.326
 I think it needs more hunger.

20:28.328 --> 20:31.796
   I have to go inside soon.
  I'm supposed to be studying.

20:31.798 --> 20:34.732
     Francis, we re in the
    middle of a film shoot.

20:34.734 --> 20:38.569
 I know, but I only got to come
out because Grandma fell asleep.

20:38.571 --> 20:41.505
      Don't you get summer
     break in home school?

20:41.507 --> 20:43.975
          Grandma says
  summer break is for farmers.

20:43.977 --> 20:47.845
       She's not going to
  be thrilled about this lawn.

20:47.847 --> 20:51.616
         Okay, maybe we
      can speed things up.

20:51.618 --> 20:54.952
    If we show the werewolf
    coming out of the coffin

20:54.954 --> 20:58.022
      then we can get rid
   of the establishing shot.

21:01.261 --> 21:02.693
            Action!

21:03.496 --> 21:04.562
            -sneeze-

21:04.564 --> 21:06.998
         Stupid thing.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.184
     What's wrong with it?

21:09.185 --> 21:11.369
      It's for magicians.
I never should have ordered it.

21:11.371 --> 21:13.804
       -FRANCIS sneezes-

21:13.806 --> 21:15.773
         Are you okay?

21:15.775 --> 21:18.376
        I may be having
       an allergy attack.

21:18.378 --> 21:20.645
   What are you allergic to?

21:20.647 --> 21:24.315
Grass, nuts, wheat, dairy, soy..

21:32.725 --> 21:40.064
  It says here that the oyster
  fork goes next to the spoon.

21:40.066 --> 21:42.033
      That can't be right.

21:42.035 --> 21:44.902
           We re not
    serving oysters, Oscar.

21:44.904 --> 21:47.838
    I'm going to go pick up
 Lu's family from the airport.

21:47.840 --> 21:50.508
     I still can't believe
    they flew out for this.

21:50.510 --> 21:51.742
    Where are they staying?

21:51.744 --> 21:54.078
I invited them to stay with us.

21:54.080 --> 21:55.079
             What?

21:55.081 --> 21:56.614
You always told me to feel free

21:56.616 --> 21:58.316
       to invite friends
       home from school!

21:58.318 --> 22:00.418
         Yeah, friends.

22:00.420 --> 22:03.754
     Not entire families of
culturally conservative lesbians

22:03.756 --> 22:04.955
 who want to marry my daughter!

22:04.957 --> 22:07.825
     It's like I told you.

22:07.826 --> 22:10.694
   Girls need a woman's touch
  or they turn out, different.

22:10.697 --> 22:14.065
   There's nothing different
   about my daughters, Marge.

22:14.067 --> 22:17.335
         Dad, could you
        buy me a coffin?

22:19.505 --> 22:22.473
          Um, no Zoe.

22:22.475 --> 22:25.843
  Why would you want a coffin?

22:25.845 --> 22:28.546
          I need one.

22:28.548 --> 22:33.050
         Zoe, only dead
      people need coffins.

22:33.052 --> 22:36.387
      Here Zoe, come help
    me with the place cards.

22:36.389 --> 22:38.389
          We re having
      company for dinner.

22:38.391 --> 22:39.557
     Can I invite Francis?

22:39.559 --> 22:41.075
             Sure.

22:41.076 --> 22:42.592
       Hey, she needs to
      take a shower first.

22:42.595 --> 22:46.731
    Zoe, go wash up and put
   on something more formal.

22:55.508 --> 22:58.576
    -KNOCKING on the window-

23:08.888 --> 23:10.788
    Hello, Mrs.McGillicuddy.

23:10.790 --> 23:12.523
   Is there something wrong?

23:12.525 --> 23:16.761
   I ll say there's something
   wrong. My dog is missing.

23:16.763 --> 23:18.529
    I'm sorry to hear that.

23:18.531 --> 23:21.532
    I know your daughter had
   something to do with this.

23:21.534 --> 23:23.534
             Zilla?

23:23.536 --> 23:26.670
The little one. With the fangs.

23:26.672 --> 23:31.742
  I'm sorry Mrs. McGillicuddy,
but Zoe doesn't even like dogs.

23:32.712 --> 23:35.146
  I didn't say she liked them.

23:35.148 --> 23:37.515
  The way she looks at Fifi...

23:37.517 --> 23:39.583
    Like that cannibal man.

23:39.585 --> 23:41.952
        Hannibal Lecter.

23:41.954 --> 23:47.024
  Mrs. McGillicuddy, I promise
 you Zoe did not eat your dog.

23:48.428 --> 23:51.462
  But we ll be sure to let you
  know if Fifi shows up, okay?

23:58.504 --> 23:59.870
            Weirdo.

23:59.872 --> 24:01.572
     Who's the weirdo, Sal?

24:01.574 --> 24:04.642
Your neighbor or your daughter?

24:10.983 --> 24:14.652
      (LIGHT PIANO MUSIC)

24:41.581 --> 24:44.849
       Zoe, I said put on
     something more formal.

24:44.851 --> 24:47.518
         Now hurry up,
      they re almost here.

24:53.159 --> 24:56.227
   Let's make sure everything
  goes well. For Zilla's sake.

24:58.064 --> 25:00.130
           (DOORBELL)

25:10.109 --> 25:11.742
            Welcome!

25:11.744 --> 25:14.812
              CORA
         We re so happy
      to finally meet you!

25:30.563 --> 25:32.796
       So I said to Luna

25:32.798 --> 25:37.268
    sweetheart, I don't care
   if you marry a man a woman

25:37.270 --> 25:40.838
        or one of those
   bizarre transgender types.

25:40.840 --> 25:43.307
  All I want are grandchildren

25:43.309 --> 25:45.643
      and with artificial
    insemination these days

25:45.645 --> 25:47.311
   that's entirely possible.

25:47.313 --> 25:52.316
 I think Zilla wants to finish
  college before she has kids.

25:52.318 --> 25:54.985
        Well, naturally!

25:54.987 --> 25:57.721
         But she won't
     want to wait too long.

25:57.723 --> 26:01.125
 I waited until I was older to
have children and quite frankly

26:01.127 --> 26:04.194
       I think something
    went wrong with my eggs.

26:06.065 --> 26:09.166
           -whisper-
   They re practically mutes.

26:11.704 --> 26:14.071
            GEOFFREY
    So you re a gay couple?

26:14.073 --> 26:17.074
             OSCAR
            Um, no.

26:17.076 --> 26:21.345
      Mm mm, no no, we re
    not any kind of couple.

26:21.347 --> 26:24.648
        That would be an
    incestuous relationship.

26:24.650 --> 26:26.050
        We re brothers.

26:26.052 --> 26:27.818
            GEOFFREY
              Hmm.

26:27.820 --> 26:30.921
You come off like a gay couple.

26:30.923 --> 26:32.590
              CORA
             Anyway

26:32.592 --> 26:35.859
     Have you thought about
what kind of ceremony you want?

26:35.861 --> 26:39.063
    Well, I think we'd like
      something very small

26:39.065 --> 26:42.166
   and informal... with just
 a few of our closest friends.

26:42.168 --> 26:46.236
     Oh. Well that wouldn't
   be very festive, would it?

26:47.940 --> 26:52.810
       Don't be afraid to
 splurge a little, sweetheart.

26:52.812 --> 26:57.281
  Geoffrey and I have decided
  we want to cover everything.

26:57.283 --> 27:01.151
       We re delighted to
     do it, aren't we dear?

27:01.153 --> 27:02.786
           Ecstatic.

27:02.788 --> 27:04.822
    Well now, wait a minute.

27:04.824 --> 27:07.224
      Why should you pay?

27:07.226 --> 27:10.127
     Well, it's traditional
     for the bride's family

27:10.129 --> 27:12.096
       to cover expenses.

27:12.098 --> 27:16.367
         Yes, but there
      are two brides here.

27:17.403 --> 27:19.937
Well I just thought that because

27:19.939 --> 27:23.140
          we re really
     extremely supportive-

27:23.142 --> 27:25.809
        Now hey, I don't
    think that's very fair.

27:25.811 --> 27:27.411
  Sal was a little taken aback

27:27.413 --> 27:29.113
      when Zilla said she
     wanted to get married

27:29.115 --> 27:30.781
    because she's so young.

27:30.783 --> 27:33.250
       That doesn't mean
      he's not supportive.

27:33.252 --> 27:35.119
     He's very supportive.

27:35.121 --> 27:37.187
            Are you?

27:39.392 --> 27:41.742
              Yes.

27:41.743 --> 27:44.093
    Sal has raised these two
  little girls all on his own

27:44.096 --> 27:47.831
and yes, he gets a little surly
 sometimes, don't get me wrong.

27:47.833 --> 27:50.067
  He has a lot of weaknesses.

27:50.069 --> 27:54.304
Frankly, he's terrifying if you
wake him up early in the morning

27:54.306 --> 27:57.708
 and if you spill just a little
    bit of furniture varnish

27:57.710 --> 28:00.444
    in the laundry machine..

28:00.446 --> 28:01.912
           watch out.

28:01.914 --> 28:02.813
           He's also-

28:02.815 --> 28:05.816
      Ahem, thanks Oscar.

28:05.818 --> 28:11.021
         But overall he
      is a very good guy.

28:11.023 --> 28:13.824
     And so if you want to
    have this competition of

28:13.826 --> 28:16.827
who's the most supportive parent

28:16.829 --> 28:20.230
    I would like to nominate
Sal as a very strong contender.

28:26.906 --> 28:29.206
       I'm not competing.

28:29.208 --> 28:34.078
      We would be happy to
  host Lu and Zilla's wedding.

28:34.947 --> 28:37.815
    And we ll do everything
   we can to make it special.

28:37.817 --> 28:42.853
      Well if we host the
   wedding, we ll go all out.

28:43.155 --> 28:47.958
       Couldn't you both
       host the wedding?

28:47.960 --> 28:50.027
            Jointly?

28:50.429 --> 28:55.833
          I suppose we
      could consider that.

28:55.835 --> 28:59.803
      This is going to be
     the best wedding since

28:59.805 --> 29:02.172
         Prince William
      and Kate Middleton!

29:02.174 --> 29:03.173
       But we don't want-

29:03.175 --> 29:04.842
   Now nonsense, sweetheart.

29:04.844 --> 29:08.112
       Everyone says they
    don't want a big wedding

29:08.114 --> 29:10.981
        but I know it's
      every girl's dream.

29:10.983 --> 29:16.053
 And I know it's hard to plan a
  wedding without your mother.

29:16.422 --> 29:19.456
        But I've always
    wanted another daughter

29:19.458 --> 29:23.260
and it doesn't look like I ll be
acquiring one via these buffoons

29:23.262 --> 29:26.430
         any time soon.

29:26.432 --> 29:28.999
         I'd be honored

29:29.001 --> 29:31.468
     if you'd try to think
      of me in that role.

29:32.905 --> 29:34.938
    I ll be your new mother.

29:34.940 --> 29:35.973
        (WINDOW SLIDES)

29:35.975 --> 29:38.542
       MRS. MCGILLICUDDY
          Mr. Balicki.

29:38.544 --> 29:41.812
         I want you to
    know that I found Fifi.

29:47.286 --> 29:48.819
             Shorn.

29:48.821 --> 29:50.487
          Humiliated.

29:50.489 --> 29:52.556
          In hiding..

29:54.493 --> 29:56.560
          Sweetheart.

30:04.537 --> 30:07.337
            -SNEEZE-

30:13.245 --> 30:15.445
              Zoe.

30:15.447 --> 30:19.016
           Did you..

30:19.018 --> 30:22.920
        shave this dog?

30:22.922 --> 30:26.423
             No...

30:26.425 --> 30:30.494
 I used your gardening shears.

30:32.031 --> 30:33.997
           That's it.

30:33.999 --> 30:36.366
      I don't know what's
   gotten into you lately but

30:36.368 --> 30:41.038
     all this horror stuff
     is getting too weird.

30:41.040 --> 30:41.939
      Give me that camera.

30:41.941 --> 30:42.940
            But Dad-

30:42.942 --> 30:46.009
          I'm serious.
         Hand it over.

30:49.515 --> 30:52.049
     No more horror films.

30:52.051 --> 30:55.118
      If you want to film
    something you can film..

30:59.925 --> 31:01.959
     your sister's wedding.

31:01.961 --> 31:04.027
         Nothing else.

31:10.102 --> 31:14.371
       (SOFT JAZZ PLAYS)

31:55.347 --> 31:57.414
           Aaaaahhh!

32:28.447 --> 32:30.447
        I need you to be
      here in ten minutes

32:30.449 --> 32:33.283
   with your werewolf costume
  and a carton of denture wax.

32:33.285 --> 32:35.085
       I ll see if I can
      skip chess practice.

32:35.087 --> 32:36.420
But how come it's so important?

32:36.422 --> 32:38.222
             Okay.

32:38.223 --> 32:40.023
 You know those severed fingers
I was marinating in the fridge?

32:40.025 --> 32:42.042
             Yeah.

32:42.043 --> 32:44.060
     Well, Lu's mother came
 downstairs dressed as a ghoul.

32:44.063 --> 32:45.963
         Why would she
     be dressed as a ghoul?

32:45.965 --> 32:47.564
   I don't know, but she was.

32:47.566 --> 32:51.501
          And she saw
   the fingers and screamed.

32:51.503 --> 32:55.105
       So I realized that
   we can make a horror film

32:55.107 --> 32:59.176
   without anybody realizing
that they re in the horror film.

33:00.679 --> 33:04.181
 I'm... so confused right now.

33:04.183 --> 33:07.250
     Never mind. Just come
  over and I ll explain later.

33:12.424 --> 33:14.324
      Did you sleep well?

33:14.326 --> 33:17.828
          MARK: Yeah.

33:17.829 --> 33:21.331
   There were a couple things
   under the cushions, but..

33:21.333 --> 33:24.001
        once I took them
      out, I slept great.

33:26.305 --> 33:28.005
            GEOFFREY
            Oh God.

33:28.006 --> 33:29.706
      Could you avoid the
 public displays of affection?

33:29.708 --> 33:30.707
         We re eating.

33:30.709 --> 33:32.542
   We just got engaged, Dad.

33:32.544 --> 33:34.544
     Be grateful we re not
making out on the coffee table.

33:34.546 --> 33:36.680
    Yes, thank you for that.

33:36.682 --> 33:38.548
    I couldn't help noticing

33:38.550 --> 33:42.285
that the pickle jar is full of..

33:42.287 --> 33:43.286
            fingers.

33:43.288 --> 33:46.023
      Oh yeah. That's Zoe.

33:46.025 --> 33:49.426
  My advice would be if you re
 squeamish about anything like

33:49.428 --> 33:51.395
      severed body parts..

33:51.397 --> 33:54.064
     never open the fridge.

33:54.066 --> 33:57.234
        Eat canned food.

33:57.236 --> 34:00.254
             Well..

34:00.255 --> 34:03.273
        This is going to
      be a marvelous day!

34:03.275 --> 34:06.309
    Wedding dress shopping!

34:06.311 --> 34:07.677
    Wedding dress shopping?

34:07.679 --> 34:10.147
           If Mom can
     incorporate  shopping

34:10.149 --> 34:12.282
         into her daily
       routine, she will.

34:12.284 --> 34:16.053
Shopping for that kind of girly
 stuff really makes me nervous.

34:16.054 --> 34:19.188
   All those perfume smells..
    and the makeup counter..

34:19.190 --> 34:22.259
      Well, we only have a
   month to plan the wedding.

34:22.261 --> 34:25.062
       Dresses take time.

34:25.063 --> 34:28.498
        Are you sure you
     don't want to rethink-

34:28.500 --> 34:30.167
              Mom.

34:30.168 --> 34:33.570
 The wedding has to be in June.

34:33.572 --> 34:35.605
  My residency starts in July.

34:35.607 --> 34:37.541
       Saturday June 30th

34:37.543 --> 34:39.109
         end of story.

34:39.110 --> 34:41.745
        Then shopping is
      definitely in order.

34:41.746 --> 34:46.817
   In fact, we'd better shop
  for the entire bridal party!

34:48.487 --> 34:52.089
    Will you be joining us?

34:52.091 --> 34:57.127
   Um, no. Thank you for the
    thought. I have to work.

34:57.429 --> 35:02.499
      Oscar will be going
 along to represent the family.

35:04.703 --> 35:08.105
        You don't work?

35:08.107 --> 35:11.141
Um, I would say I'm temporarily

35:11.143 --> 35:15.445
         on a leave of
 absence from official duties.

35:15.447 --> 35:17.347
       You re unemployed.

35:17.349 --> 35:20.817
       This is Portland.
  Unemployment is more like...

35:22.754 --> 35:25.755
          an art form.

35:25.757 --> 35:28.391
      Can I come shopping?

35:28.393 --> 35:31.661
           I'm sorry,
    you want to go shopping?

35:31.663 --> 35:34.297
       And since we ll be
      doing wedding stuff

35:34.299 --> 35:38.802
      I ll need my camera.

35:38.804 --> 35:40.871
          I can shoot
     the wedding planning.

35:40.873 --> 35:42.405
      Like a documentary.

35:42.407 --> 35:46.510
             OSCAR
 Documentaries are educational.

35:46.512 --> 35:49.412
             Fine.

35:49.414 --> 35:52.415
      But I don't want any
  weird horror stuff, alright?

35:52.417 --> 35:53.850
     Have you thought about

35:53.852 --> 35:56.686
       who's going to be
     in your bridal party?

35:56.688 --> 35:59.106
            Oh yes.

35:59.107 --> 36:01.525
   Well of course Matt, Mark
 and John will be on Lu's side.

36:01.527 --> 36:04.261
  And on my side I ll have my
 two best friends from Portland

36:04.263 --> 36:05.428
         Pat and Angie.

36:05.430 --> 36:07.831
        And Zoe's going
     to be my flower girl!

36:07.833 --> 36:09.900
          -BARF sound-

36:21.680 --> 36:23.513
          You re Pat.

36:23.515 --> 36:24.681
            Patrick.

36:24.683 --> 36:26.550
   It's so nice to meet you.

36:26.552 --> 36:30.921
      Oh, no. Sorry guys,
    but I promised your dad.

36:30.923 --> 36:33.590
     No more horror stuff.

36:38.664 --> 36:42.299
      (UPTEMPO, FUN JAZZ)

36:52.244 --> 36:54.244
          How much to
     unlock the rental car?

36:54.246 --> 36:56.713
              MATT
      How about ten bucks?

36:56.715 --> 36:58.648
    We don't have that much.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.717
    Maybe you could earn it.

37:00.719 --> 37:02.485
   What would we have to do?

37:02.487 --> 37:05.922
I think a good prank would be a
timely diversion right about now

37:05.924 --> 37:07.657
    I don't know any pranks.

37:07.659 --> 37:10.727
  You ll have to think of one.

37:12.965 --> 37:15.616
             Okay.

37:15.617 --> 37:18.268
  What if we go into the shop
 and hide everybody's clothes?

37:18.270 --> 37:20.337
     And when they re done
    trying on wedding stuff,

37:20.339 --> 37:25.675
   all their clothes will be
 gone and everyone will scream.

37:25.677 --> 37:27.744
           You re on.

37:41.526 --> 37:44.427
 There's my little flower girl!

37:44.429 --> 37:46.496
      We've got to get you
     into your dress, dear.

37:58.377 --> 38:00.977
 Um, where do I put my clothes?

38:00.979 --> 38:04.047
           SALES LADY
      We can put them in a
   garment bag for you, dear.

38:11.790 --> 38:16.693
       (MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)

38:36.615 --> 38:39.849
       Alright, I did it.
     Now give me the keys.

38:39.851 --> 38:41.651
          Nice dress.

38:41.653 --> 38:43.553
          I'd keep the
    comments about the dress

38:43.555 --> 38:46.022
  to a minimum if I were you.

38:53.432 --> 38:56.566
       Okay. The werewolf
 just climbed out of his coffin

38:56.568 --> 38:59.069
       and he's wandering
      around town lonely.

38:59.071 --> 39:01.438
       He wants friends.

39:01.439 --> 39:03.806
But no one will be friends with
  him because he's a monster.

39:03.809 --> 39:07.744
The only way he can make friends
is if they become monsters too.

39:07.746 --> 39:09.412
   So he has to bite someone.

39:09.414 --> 39:12.916
            Action.

39:12.918 --> 39:16.486
     Now that is adorable.

39:16.488 --> 39:20.590
  Oh, and what about this one?

39:20.592 --> 39:23.526
           SALES LADY
    Would you like to try a
   mother-of-the-bride dress?

39:23.528 --> 39:26.730
   Ooh, that would be lovely!

39:32.671 --> 39:34.704
         I don't know,
      it's kind of dumpy.

39:34.706 --> 39:35.905
 I don't feel like any of these

39:35.907 --> 39:43.079
       really capture my
       true personality.

39:43.081 --> 39:45.482
   You have to get higher up.

40:04.569 --> 40:07.637
         But this would
      look lovely on you!

40:07.639 --> 40:10.473
         Mom, you know
     I don't wear dresses.

40:10.475 --> 40:12.976
       You don't normally
     get married either Lu

40:12.978 --> 40:15.578
      but I was hoping you
    could make an exception

40:15.580 --> 40:18.448
          for the most
  elaborate day of your life.

40:18.450 --> 40:20.550
          Now darling

40:20.552 --> 40:24.721
        this would look
