 masks and do a monster dance?

58:01.946 --> 58:04.713
       It's really easy.
   Francis choreographed it.

58:04.715 --> 58:06.248
              CORA
    What I don't understand

58:06.250 --> 58:10.185
      is why they were so
   upset about a little thing

58:10.187 --> 58:14.122
       like breaking the
       Ten Commandments.

58:14.124 --> 58:17.226
       Everyone breaks a
  commandment sooner or later.

58:17.228 --> 58:19.127
It's not like it's a mortal sin.

58:19.129 --> 58:22.998
   Actually I think it's the
  definition of a mortal sin.

58:23.000 --> 58:25.667
 Well, maybe it's for the best.

58:26.537 --> 58:28.136
    What do you mean, Zill?

58:28.138 --> 58:31.807
I mean, maybe my dad was right.

58:31.809 --> 58:33.175
We barely even know each other.

58:33.177 --> 58:35.978
         I didn't even
   know you were a Christian.

58:35.980 --> 58:37.946
      That's not the most
   important thing about me.

58:37.948 --> 58:39.147
     And we never discussed

58:39.149 --> 58:41.683
        how we re going
     to raise our children

58:41.685 --> 58:43.785
       We don't even know
 if we re gonna have children.

58:43.787 --> 58:47.089
       And everyone in my
     family gets a divorce!

58:47.091 --> 58:49.925
     Hey, hey, but it's not
      without good reason.

58:49.927 --> 58:53.262
          I mean, your
 grandparents had a fundamental

58:53.264 --> 58:57.165
difference of opinion regarding
  the definition of  monogamy

58:57.167 --> 59:00.102
          and my wife?

59:00.104 --> 59:05.073
            She was,
   quite frankly, psychotic.

59:07.011 --> 59:09.545
             Zilla.

59:09.547 --> 59:11.046
     Ever since we started
     planning this wedding

59:11.048 --> 59:13.715
   you haven't been yourself.

59:15.052 --> 59:18.320
        (CRYING SOUNDS)

59:25.262 --> 59:29.131
        What's going on?

59:30.067 --> 59:34.269
       Zoe, what is this?

59:35.239 --> 59:39.308
    It's not enough that you
 humiliated us at church today?

59:39.310 --> 59:42.010
  It's not enough that you re
 ruining your sister's wedding?

59:42.012 --> 59:45.714
   Can't you see how unhappy
   you re making your sister?

59:47.651 --> 59:51.153
          I am ashamed
I ever let you buy this camera.

59:51.155 --> 59:55.057
      I am ashamed that I
   didn't put a stop to this

59:55.059 --> 59:58.994
        horror business
     the moment it started.

59:58.996 --> 01:00:01.129
      You know what, Zoe?

01:00:01.131 --> 01:00:04.199
        I guess I'm just
        ashamed of you.

01:00:42.139 --> 01:00:43.705
      What are you doing?

01:00:43.707 --> 01:00:45.707
          I'm leaving.

01:00:45.709 --> 01:00:46.842
           How come?

01:00:46.844 --> 01:00:50.112
         You heard him!
      He's ashamed of me.

01:00:50.114 --> 01:00:54.182
       Where will you go?

01:00:54.184 --> 01:00:56.718
       I ll stay at your
   house tonight, and then..

01:00:56.720 --> 01:00:58.420
   I ll go live with my mom.

01:00:58.422 --> 01:01:00.155
 Do you even know where she is?

01:01:00.157 --> 01:01:03.692
     No, but I ll find her.

01:01:03.694 --> 01:01:06.795
  What about the horror film?

01:01:06.797 --> 01:01:09.264
           It's over.

01:01:16.774 --> 01:01:19.775
     -he grunts and groans-

01:01:33.691 --> 01:01:37.926
          We need help
   locating a missing person.

01:01:38.896 --> 01:01:41.029
      Does this appear to
  be a police station to you?

01:01:41.031 --> 01:01:44.366
 No, but you re the only adult
  we know who's talking to us.

01:01:44.368 --> 01:01:47.002
      Well, I do happen to
     be an expert on crime.

01:01:47.004 --> 01:01:49.471
This person isn't a criminal...

01:01:50.274 --> 01:01:51.773
           we think.

01:01:51.775 --> 01:01:53.075
        Well, who is it?

01:01:53.077 --> 01:01:54.843
            Her mom.

01:01:54.845 --> 01:01:56.144
     Your mother's missing?

01:01:56.146 --> 01:01:57.145
              Yes.

01:01:57.147 --> 01:01:58.213
         For how long?

01:01:58.215 --> 01:01:59.948
        About ten years.

01:01:59.950 --> 01:02:01.249
        How old are you?

01:02:01.251 --> 01:02:03.085
              Ten.

01:02:03.087 --> 01:02:04.319
             I see.

01:02:04.321 --> 01:02:06.188
        So this isn't so
     much a  missing person

01:02:06.190 --> 01:02:07.989
     as it is a  person who
    intentionally abandoned

01:02:07.991 --> 01:02:09.958
        her daughter and
     hasn't been seen since

01:02:09.960 --> 01:02:10.926
         is that right?

01:02:10.928 --> 01:02:12.027
              Yes.

01:02:12.029 --> 01:02:13.212
And has it occurred to you that

01:02:13.213 --> 01:02:14.396
         she might have
    done this for a reason?

01:02:14.398 --> 01:02:16.215
         As in, rather
     than failing to share

01:02:16.216 --> 01:02:18.033
   this information with you
  because it slipped her mind

01:02:18.035 --> 01:02:19.468
       she may have made
     a deliberate decision

01:02:19.470 --> 01:02:20.902
        that she doesn't
      want to be bothered

01:02:20.904 --> 01:02:22.471
     by a sniveling cretin
    who can't even remember

01:02:22.473 --> 01:02:24.005
to clean under her fingernails?

01:02:24.007 --> 01:02:26.041
        You don't clean
    under your fingernails!

01:02:26.043 --> 01:02:27.226
             DWAYNE
          Digression!

01:02:27.227 --> 01:02:28.410
       You re completely
    drifting from the point.

01:02:28.412 --> 01:02:29.945
          Your mother
     doesn't even know me.

01:02:29.947 --> 01:02:32.247
    Try to be more logical.

01:02:32.249 --> 01:02:34.182
 We just want help finding her.

01:02:34.184 --> 01:02:36.418
      Look, if your mother
    doesn't want to meet you

01:02:36.420 --> 01:02:38.787
forcing the acquaintance on her
  is not the kind of situation

01:02:38.789 --> 01:02:40.856
      that's going to lead
     to love and cupcakes.

01:02:40.858 --> 01:02:43.759
      Meanwhile, I've been
  working on your horror film.

01:02:43.761 --> 01:02:45.444
        I've designed a
       trip wedding cake

01:02:45.445 --> 01:02:47.128
     that when you cut into
   it, it spurts fake blood.

01:02:47.131 --> 01:02:49.765
         You wanna see?

01:02:49.767 --> 01:02:51.833
           We re here
        for information.

01:02:51.835 --> 01:02:52.868
             Fine.

01:02:52.870 --> 01:02:54.803
            Have you
       checked Facebook?

01:02:54.805 --> 01:02:56.338
  She doesn't have an account.

01:02:56.340 --> 01:02:57.539
             DWAYNE
     Well when I was a boy

01:02:57.541 --> 01:02:59.007
           we had an
   old-fashioned device known

01:02:59.009 --> 01:03:00.475
     as a  telephone book.

01:03:00.477 --> 01:03:02.944
       You could look up
addresses in a small metal hovel

01:03:02.946 --> 01:03:04.880
           known as a
        telephone booth.

01:03:04.882 --> 01:03:07.115
    There's one conveniently
  located at the bus station.

01:03:07.117 --> 01:03:12.053
     You could look her up
    and get right on a bus..

01:03:12.055 --> 01:03:13.922
         I suggest you
    avoid this step though!

01:03:13.924 --> 01:03:15.857
      You re only setting
     yourself up for pain.

01:03:15.859 --> 01:03:17.425
      I have to find her.

01:03:17.427 --> 01:03:19.294
    My dad doesn't love me.

01:03:19.296 --> 01:03:21.363
       Actually, I'd say

01:03:21.364 --> 01:03:23.431
 all evidence so far points to
  your mother not loving you.

01:03:23.433 --> 01:03:26.201
Although I suppose it's possible
    that neither of them do.

01:03:26.203 --> 01:03:28.220
       What do you know?

01:03:28.221 --> 01:03:30.238
     The only thing you re
    good at is horror stuff!

01:03:32.509 --> 01:03:35.177
             I also
      specialize in magic!

01:03:56.266 --> 01:03:59.968
         I never wanted
       to be like my mom.

01:03:59.970 --> 01:04:01.603
          You re not.

01:04:01.605 --> 01:04:03.605
        How do you know?

01:04:03.607 --> 01:04:05.524
    My dad's been telling me

01:04:05.525 --> 01:04:07.442
   my whole life not to rush
  into things but I always do.

01:04:07.444 --> 01:04:09.344
         Just like her.

01:04:09.346 --> 01:04:11.880
She rushed into getting married

01:04:11.882 --> 01:04:13.348
          when she was
      too young to commit

01:04:13.350 --> 01:04:14.916
         and she rushed
      into having children

01:04:14.918 --> 01:04:17.118
       before she was old
     enough to realize that

01:04:17.120 --> 01:04:20.422
    she didn't even want us.

01:04:20.424 --> 01:04:23.258
       So marriage didn't
       work out for her.

01:04:23.260 --> 01:04:25.627
 It works out for some people.

01:04:25.629 --> 01:04:28.063
        It will for us.

01:04:28.065 --> 01:04:30.465
        How do you know?

01:04:30.467 --> 01:04:32.534
           I just do.

01:04:34.037 --> 01:04:35.370
       That doesn't seem
       like a good enough

01:04:35.372 --> 01:04:38.974
reason to go through with this.

01:04:38.976 --> 01:04:40.408
         You know what?
         You re right.

01:04:40.410 --> 01:04:42.944
    You do rush into things.

01:04:42.946 --> 01:04:46.414
     You rushed into trying
    out for the soccer team

01:04:46.416 --> 01:04:48.617
         when you were
        only a freshman.

01:04:48.619 --> 01:04:52.587
     And you made varsity.
    You rushed into pre-med.

01:04:52.589 --> 01:04:55.991
    And now you re on track
    to graduate with honors.

01:04:55.993 --> 01:05:01.129
     It's one of the things
     that I love about you.

01:05:01.131 --> 01:05:04.633
You re impulsive and passionate

01:05:04.635 --> 01:05:07.903
     and you jump into the
    things you care about..

01:05:07.905 --> 01:05:11.907
     and see them through.

01:05:14.645 --> 01:05:17.245
  Why would marriage work for
  me when it hasn't worked out

01:05:17.247 --> 01:05:20.615
           for anyone
       else in my family?

01:05:20.617 --> 01:05:22.584
  I think marriage would have
    worked out for your dad

01:05:22.586 --> 01:05:26.221
    if he'd married somebody
a little bit more like himself.

01:05:26.223 --> 01:05:29.157
        Look how well he
    did raising you and Zoe

01:05:29.159 --> 01:05:31.626
        all by himself.

01:05:31.628 --> 01:05:35.630
       You don't think we
   turned out kind of weird?

01:05:35.632 --> 01:05:39.167
          Yeah, I do.

01:05:39.169 --> 01:05:42.370
  You re weird when you laugh.

01:05:42.372 --> 01:05:46.274
    It's weird when you eat
  leftover soup for breakfast.

01:05:46.276 --> 01:05:51.179
You have this weird little dent

01:05:51.181 --> 01:05:54.649
          on your lip
     from when you bite it.

01:06:01.058 --> 01:06:05.360
         I love all the
    weird things about you.

01:06:05.362 --> 01:06:09.030
       That's how I know
     you re the one for me.

01:06:09.032 --> 01:06:12.701
      I love all the weird
     things about you, too.

01:06:12.703 --> 01:06:15.403
    Then let's get married.

01:06:27.985 --> 01:06:31.486
      Are we to understand
     the wedding's back on?

01:06:34.458 --> 01:06:36.992
         And where's it
      going to take place?

01:06:36.994 --> 01:06:39.995
         We thought we
  could just get married here.

01:06:39.997 --> 01:06:43.298
    That's a fabulous idea.

01:06:43.300 --> 01:06:46.301
        I'm picturing..

01:06:46.303 --> 01:06:49.371
             swans.
          On the lawn.

01:06:52.209 --> 01:06:54.042
           By the way

01:06:54.044 --> 01:06:58.046
        I couldn't help
   noticing that Zoe's gone.

01:06:58.048 --> 01:07:00.148
    What do you mean, gone?

01:07:00.150 --> 01:07:03.051
    Well I went upstairs to
  press her flower girl dress

01:07:03.053 --> 01:07:04.452
     and she wasn't there.

01:07:04.454 --> 01:07:06.554
      The bed didn't look
   like it had been slept in.

01:07:06.556 --> 01:07:08.456
      Maybe she ran away.

01:07:08.458 --> 01:07:10.291
She was pretty upset last night.

01:07:10.293 --> 01:07:14.329
  Did it look like she packed
    her clothes or anything?

01:07:14.331 --> 01:07:18.400
  No, but that vampire poster
   on her wall was missing..

01:07:21.338 --> 01:07:24.506
       Frankly, I felt it
   looked better without it.

01:07:24.508 --> 01:07:26.574
   You two search the house.

01:07:26.576 --> 01:07:29.244
     I ll go find Francis.

01:07:33.517 --> 01:07:37.318
        Duh nuh nuh nuh!
   Duh nuh nuh nuh! Duh nuh!

01:07:43.226 --> 01:07:45.660
    Uh, two in one morning!
    This is really too much.

01:07:45.662 --> 01:07:48.430
       I can't deal with
  these kind of interruptions.

01:07:48.432 --> 01:07:52.767
      Oh. It's you again.
       What do you want?

01:07:52.769 --> 01:07:54.135
          Do you know
          my daughter?

01:07:54.137 --> 01:07:55.804
          Zoe Balicki.

01:07:55.806 --> 01:07:57.806
            I might.

01:07:57.808 --> 01:08:02.444
     She's about this tall,
and she always carries a camera.

01:08:02.446 --> 01:08:05.713
         She's not dead
      or anything, is she?

01:08:05.715 --> 01:08:06.748
         Of course not.

01:08:06.750 --> 01:08:09.350
             Fine.
   She came in this morning.

01:08:09.352 --> 01:08:13.521
       Yes, I believe she
   was asking you for advice?

01:08:13.523 --> 01:08:16.323
        A lot of people
       ask me for advice.

01:08:16.326 --> 01:08:18.493
      I can't always keep
   track of what I tell them.

01:08:18.495 --> 01:08:20.328
       You told Zoe to go
     to the bus station and

01:08:20.330 --> 01:08:21.696
        look up her mom
       in the phone book

01:08:21.698 --> 01:08:24.232
     and then you said she-

01:08:24.234 --> 01:08:26.667
       Listen, we re not
   accusing you of anything.

01:08:26.670 --> 01:08:28.886
   We just want to find her.

01:08:28.888 --> 01:08:31.104
    Well, then I suggest you
 take the advice of this small

01:08:31.108 --> 01:08:34.609
    flesh-eating carnivore,
   and call the bus station.

01:08:34.611 --> 01:08:38.279
     I'm dialing right now.

01:08:38.281 --> 01:08:42.317
      You know, I wouldn't
    say this to her face but

01:08:43.252 --> 01:08:44.853
your daughter's fairly talented.

01:08:44.854 --> 01:08:47.139
   I've seen her horror films

01:08:47.140 --> 01:08:49.424
   and she has the potential
     to really be someone.

01:08:49.426 --> 01:08:50.792
       Someone like you?

01:08:50.794 --> 01:08:53.461
     I have chosen to focus
  my talents in other spheres

01:08:53.462 --> 01:08:56.865
       such as the retail
         industry and..

01:08:56.867 --> 01:08:58.832
             magic.

01:08:58.835 --> 01:09:02.604
      but I believe she's
primarily interested in horror.

01:09:02.606 --> 01:09:06.140
  Yeah, well sorry if  horror

01:09:06.143 --> 01:09:09.344
       doesn't sound like
     a viable career path.

01:09:09.345 --> 01:09:11.479
         It worked out
      for Stanley Kubrick.

01:09:11.481 --> 01:09:13.314
          They didn't
     sell her a bus ticket.

01:09:13.316 --> 01:09:15.483
          Okay, look.

01:09:15.484 --> 01:09:17.651
      If her mother wasn't
   listed in the phone book,

01:09:17.652 --> 01:09:19.819
   do you have any idea where
   else she might have gone?

01:09:19.823 --> 01:09:23.291
        I might know one
   other place she might be.

01:09:34.871 --> 01:09:35.937
            ACTIVIST
      Keep Portland weird!

01:09:35.939 --> 01:09:39.207
             Yeah,
  we got that covered, thanks.

01:10:04.467 --> 01:10:07.268
              Zoe.

01:10:07.270 --> 01:10:10.438
            Come on.
       We re going home.

01:10:15.378 --> 01:10:19.781
              Hey!
      I just got in line.

01:10:19.783 --> 01:10:22.884
     I can't believe we re
    actually going to Vegas!

01:10:22.886 --> 01:10:23.885
         Neither can I.

01:10:23.887 --> 01:10:26.821
 Best bachelorette party ever!

01:10:26.823 --> 01:10:29.224
        Well, naturally.
         I planned it.

01:10:29.226 --> 01:10:30.992
    I still think it's weird
  that the mother of the bride

01:10:30.994 --> 01:10:33.695
     is going along on her
 daughter's bachelorette party.

01:10:33.697 --> 01:10:35.797
        Anything to get
     her out of the house.

01:10:35.799 --> 01:10:37.932
          Why can't I
          go to Vegas?

01:10:37.934 --> 01:10:40.868
          (a) Because
     you re still grounded

01:10:40.870 --> 01:10:43.771
        for running away
       from home and (b)

01:10:43.773 --> 01:10:46.874
  Because ten-year-olds don't
 go to these kinds of events..

01:10:46.876 --> 01:10:48.977
I want you to be careful, okay?

01:10:48.979 --> 01:10:51.279
           Vegas is a
        dangerous place.

01:10:51.281 --> 01:10:53.248
Do not come back with pink eye.

01:10:53.250 --> 01:10:55.783
    You do not want pink eye
 in all your wedding pictures.

01:10:55.785 --> 01:10:56.985
              Dad!
       That's disgusting.

01:10:56.987 --> 01:10:59.320
         Yeah. Exactly.
     It's very disgusting.

01:10:59.322 --> 01:11:00.955
         But it happens
      at bachelor parties,

01:11:00.957 --> 01:11:02.824
        and I'm assuming
        it can happen at

01:11:02.826 --> 01:11:04.826
     lesbian bachelorettes.

01:11:04.828 --> 01:11:06.427
   Your eye will swell up and

01:11:06.429 --> 01:11:08.997
        you ll look like
      a zombie who is ill.

01:11:08.999 --> 01:11:13.401
    How do you get pink eye?

